data.title: Kyle Korver Player Profile, Milwaukee Bucks
data.meta_description: Get the latest news, stats and more about Kyle Korver on RealGM.com
data.text: Jun 26, 2003 - The New Jersey Nets selected Kyle Korver in Round 2 with Pick 22 in the 2003 NBA Draft. Jun 26, 2003 - The draft rights to Kyle Korver was acquired by the Philadelphia Sixers from the New Jersey Nets in exchange for cash. Aug 8, 2003 - Kyle Korver signed a multi-year contract with the Philadelphia Sixers. Jun 28, 2005 - The Philadelphia Sixers tendered a Qualifying Offer to make Kyle Korver a Restricted FA. Jul 1, 2005 - Kyle Korver, previously with the Philadelphia Sixers, became a free agent. Aug 11, 2005 - Kyle Korver signed a multi-year contract with the Philadelphia Sixers. Dec 29, 2007 - Kyle Korver was acquired by the Utah Jazz from the Philadelphia Sixers in exchange for Gordan Giricek, a More Favorable 2009 1st round pick, a Least Favorable 2010 1st round pick and a conditional 2011 1st round pick (UTH own). Jul 1, 2010 - Kyle Korver, previously with the Utah Jazz, became a free agent. Jul 9, 2010 - Kyle Korver signed a multi-year contract with the Chicago Bulls. Jul 16, 2012 - Kyle Korver was acquired by the Atlanta Hawks from the Chicago Bulls in exchange for cash and a TPE. Jul 1, 2013 - Kyle Korver, previously with the Atlanta Hawks, became a free agent. Jul 11, 2013 - Kyle Korver signed a multi-year contract with the Atlanta Hawks. Jan 7, 2017 - Kyle Korver was acquired by the Cleveland Cavaliers, along with multiple TPEs, from the Atlanta Hawks in exchange for Mike Dunleavy, Mo Williams, a conditional 2019 1st round pick (CLE own), cash and a TPE. Jul 1, 2017 - Kyle Korver, previously with the Cleveland Cavaliers, became a free agent. Jul 12, 2017 - Kyle Korver signed a multi-year contract with the Cleveland Cavaliers. Nov 29, 2018 - Kyle Korver was acquired by the Utah Jazz, along with a TPE, from the Cleveland Cavaliers in exchange for Alec Burks, a 2020 2nd round pick (UTH own) and a 2021 2nd round pick (WAS own). Jul 6, 2019 - Kyle Korver was acquired by the Memphis Grizzlies, along with Grayson Allen, Jae Crowder, the draft rights to Darius Bazley, a conditional 2020 1st round pick (UTH own) and a TPE, from the Utah Jazz in exchange for Mike Conley and multiple TPEs. Jul 7, 2019 - Kyle Korver was acquired by the Phoenix Suns, along with Jevon Carter, from the Memphis Grizzlies in exchange for Josh Jackson, De'Anthony Melton, a conditional 2021 2nd round pick (PHX own) and a 2020 2nd round pick (PHX own). Jul 8, 2019 - The Phoenix Suns placed the contract of Kyle Korver on waivers. Jul 10, 2019 - Kyle Korver, previously with the Phoenix Suns, became a free agent. Jul 25, 2019 - Kyle Korver signed a contract with the Milwaukee Bucks. Nov 21, 2020 - Kyle Korver, previously with the Milwaukee Bucks, became a free agent.
